Working at Bank of Hawaii
Benefits
FAQ



At Bank of Hawaii, our goal is to serve our customers and communities by providing creative and cutting edge financial services. The core of our success is our dedicated employees, who continuously provide inspirational and innovative solutions to guide us into 21st century banking. Join Bank of Hawaii, your opportunity for a rewarding career awaits. 
 

 COMMUNITY > 
 PHILANTHROPY > 

 
We are committed to fully complying in letter and in spirit with all Equal Opportunity Employment and Affirmative Action laws and regulations. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment and will not be discriminated against on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, including gender identify or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, citizenship, ancestry, age, marital status, genetic information, domestic or sexual violence victim status, disability, protected veteran status or any other status protected by federal, state or local law. Bank of Hawaii takes affirmative action in support of its policy to advance in employment individuals who are minorities, women, protected veterans, and individuals with disabilities. We also foster a drug-free work environment. 








