BOH Profile | Bank of Hawaii Corporation Stock - Yahoo FinanceHomeMailFlickrTumblrNewsSportsFinanceCelebrityAnswersGroupsMobileMoreYahooSearchSearch0U.S. Markets open in 27 mins.S&P Futures2,478.75+4.75 (+0.19%)Dow Futures21,633.00+73.00 (+0.34%)Bank of Hawaii Corporation (BOH)NYSE - NYSE Delayed Price. Currency in USDAdd to watchlist85.29+1.72 (+2.06%)At close:  4:02PM EDTPeople also watchCFRBXSCBSHBOKFCPFSummaryConversationsStatisticsProfileFinancialsOptionsHoldersHistorical DataAnalystsBank of Hawaii Corporation130 Merchant StreetHonolulu, HI 96813United States888-643-3888http://www.boh.comSector: FinancialIndustry: Regional - Pacific BanksFull Time Employees: 2,115Key ExecutivesNameTitlePayExercisedAgeMr. Peter S. HoChairman, Chief Exec. Officer, Pres and Director of Bank of Hawali2.93MN/A52Mr. Kent T. LucienVice Chairman, Chief Strategy Officer, Director and Director of Bank of Hawaii1.22M423.43k63Mr. Mark A. RossiVice Chairman, Chief Admin. Officer, Gen. Counsel and Corp. Sec.1.22MN/A68Ms. Mary E. SellersVice Chairman and Chief Risk Officer1.2MN/A60Mr. Wayne Y. HamanoVice Chairman and Chief Commercial Officer981.22kN/A62Amounts are as of December 31, 2016 and compensation values are for the last fiscal year ending on that date. Pay is salary, bonuses, etc. Exercised is the value of options exercised during the fiscal year. Currency in USD.DescriptionBank of Hawaii Corporation operates as the holding company for Bank of Hawaii that provides financial products and services in Hawaii, Guam, and other Pacific Islands. The company operates through four segments: Retail Banking, Commercial Banking, Investment Services, and Treasury and Other. The Retail Banking segment offers financial products and services to consumers and small businesses. It offers checking, savings, and time deposit accounts; loan and lease products, such as residential mortgage loans, home equity lines of credit, automobile loans and leases, personal lines of credit, installment loans, small business loans and leases, and credit cards; and retail insurance products. This segment provides its products and services through 69 branch locations and 449 ATMs in Hawaii and the Pacific Islands, as well as through a customer service center, and online and mobile banking. The Commercial Banking segments product lines comprise corporate banking, commercial real estate loans, commercial lease financing, auto dealer financing, and deposit products. It offers commercial lending and deposit products to middle-market and large companies; and commercial real estate mortgages to investors, developers, and builders. This segment also provides international banking services; and merchant services to small business customers. The Investment Services segment provides private banking and international client banking, trust, investment management, and institutional investment advisory services. It serves individuals and families, high-net-worth individuals, corporations, government entities, and foundations. This segment also provides brokerage services, such as equities, mutual funds, life insurance, and annuity products. The Treasury and Other segment offers corporate asset and liability management services, such as interest rate risk management and foreign exchange services. Bank of Hawaii Corporation was founded in 1897 and is headquartered in Honolulu, Hawaii.Corporate GovernanceBank of Hawaii Corporation’s ISS Governance QualityScore as of July 1, 2017 is 1. The pillar scores are Audit: 1; Board: 2; Shareholder Rights: 2; Compensation: 1.Corporate governance scores courtesy of Institutional Shareholder Services (ISS).  Scores indicate decile rank relative to index or region. A decile score of 1 indicates lower governance risk, while a 10 indicates higher governance risk.Yahoo Small BusinessData DisclaimerHelpSuggestionsPrivacyAbout Our AdsTerms (Updated)







