Bank of Hawaii Corporation Key Developments

Bank of Hawaii Corporation Announces Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Reports Net Loan and Lease Charge-Offs for the Second Quarter of 2017
Jul 24 17
Bank of Hawaii Corporation announced consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. The company reported diluted earnings per share of $1.05 for the second quarter of 2017, down from diluted earnings per share of $1.20 in the previous quarter and up from diluted earnings per share of $1.03 in the same quarter last year. Net income for the second quarter of 2017 was $44.7 million compared with net income of $51.2 million in the first quarter of 2017 and net income of $44.2 million in the second quarter of 2016. The return on average assets for the second quarter of 2017 was 1.09%, down from 1.26% in the previous quarter and 1.14% in the same quarter last year. The return on average equity for the second quarter of 2017 was 14.87%, down from 17.63% for the first quarter of 2017 and 15.56% in the second quarter of 2016. Net interest income, on a taxable equivalent basis, for the second quarter of 2017 was $115.3 million, an increase of $2.4 million compared with net interest income of $112.9 million in the first quarter of 2017 and an increase of $8.8 million compared with net interest income of $106.5 million in the second quarter of 2016. Income before provision for income taxes was $65.076 million compared to $62.998 million a year ago. 

For the six-month period ended June 30, 2017, net income was $95.8 million, an increase of $1.4 million from net income of $94.5 million during the same period last year. Diluted earnings per share were $2.24 for the first half of 2017, an increase from diluted earnings per share of $2.19 for the first half of 2016. The return on average assets for the six-month period ended June 30, 2017 was 1.17% compared with 1.22% for the same six months in 2016. The year-to-date return on average equity was 16.22% for the first half of 2017 compared with 16.71% for the six month period ended June 30, 2016. Net interest income for the first half of 2017 was $228.3 million, an increase of $15.7 million compared with net interest income of $212.6 million for the first half of 2016. Book value per share was $28.45 compared to $26.96 a year ago. Book value per share was $27.72 compared to $26.23 a year ago. Income before provision for income taxes was $137.896 million compared to $136.843 million a year ago. 

Net loan and lease charge-offs during the second quarter of 2017 were $3.0 million or 0.13% annualized of total average loans and leases outstanding. Loan and lease charge-offs of $5.5 million during the quarter were partially offset by recoveries of $2.5 million. Net charge-offs during the second quarter of 2016 were $1.7 million or 0.09% annualized of total average loans and leases outstanding and comprised of $3.7 million in charge-offs and recoveries of $2.0 million.


Bank of Hawaii Corporation Declares Quarterly Cash Dividend for the Second Quarter Ended March 31, 2017, Payable on September 15, 2017
Jul 24 17
Bank of Hawaii Corporation declared a quarterly cash dividend of $0.52 per share on the company's outstanding shares for the second quarter ended March 31, 2017. The dividend will be payable on September 15, 2017 to shareholders of record at the close of business on August 31, 2017.


Bank of Hawaii Corporation to Report Q2, 2017 Results on Jul 24, 2017
Jul 5 17
Bank of Hawaii Corporation announced that they will report Q2, 2017 results Pre-Market on Jul 24, 2017


